The paper deals with the problem of salient object detection in images, which is a well-studied problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed approach involves modeling the image as a hypergraph, which is a mathematical structure commonly used in machine learning and data mining (cs.AI). The paper also proposes an alternative approach based on support vector machines (SVMs), which is a popular machine learning technique (cs.LG). The experimental results involve the use of several image datasets, which are commonly used in computer vision research (cs.MM). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of contextual properties of image pixels or regions, which is a topic of interest in graph theory and network analysis (cs.GR).
